Design spec:

LAYOUT:
Single unified table with these columns:
  Row # | [all data columns from File A] | [same columns from File B]

The table has two halves — left half is File A, right half
is File B. Column headers appear once on each side.

Like this (simplified to 3 columns):

┌─────┬──────────┬────────────┬──────────┬──────────┬────────────┬──────────┐
│ Row │          │  FILE A    │          │          │  FILE B    │          │
├─────┼──────────┼────────────┼──────────┼──────────┼────────────┼──────────┤
│     │ emp_id   │ status     │ salary   │ emp_id   │ status     │ salary   │
├─────┼──────────┼────────────┼──────────┼──────────┼────────────┼──────────┤
│  1  │ EMP0001  │ active     │ 75000    │ EMP0001  │ active     │ 75000    │  ← unchanged, greyed
│  2  │ EMP0002  │ verified   │ 90000    │ EMP0002  │ suspended  │ 90000    │  ← modified, amber row
│  3  │ EMP0003  │ -          │ -        │ EMP0003  │ active     │ 55000    │  ← added, green row
│  4  │ EMP0004  │ inactive   │ 45000    │ EMP0004  │ -          │ -        │  ← deleted, red row
└─────┴──────────┴────────────┴──────────┴──────────┴────────────┴──────────┘

ROW COLOURS (full row, both sides):
- Unchanged:  no colour change, opacity 0.5 (greyed out)
- Modified:   amber/yellow background  #92400e or similar dark amber
              both the File A and File B halves coloured amber
- Added:      green background  #14532d or similar dark green
              File A side shows "—" for all cells (row didn't exist)
              File B side shows the actual values
- Deleted:    red background  #7f1d1d or similar dark red
              File A side shows the actual values
              File B side shows "—" for all cells

CHANGED CELLS within modified rows:
- The specific cells that changed get a brighter highlight
- File A changed cell: slightly brighter red tint within the amber row
- File B changed cell: slightly brighter green tint within the amber row
- Unchanged cells within a modified row: normal amber

HEADER:
Two section headers spanning the column groups:
  "File A — [filename]"    spanning left columns
  "File B — [filename]"    spanning right columns

SUMMARY BAR above the table:
  +X added  |  -X deleted  |  ~X modified  |  X unchanged
  Each count in its respective colour

CONTROLS above the table:
  [ ] Show unchanged rows (checkbox, checked by default)
      When unchecked: hide greyed rows, show only changes
  [ ] Highlight changed cells (checkbox, checked by default)

STICKY HEADER:
Column headers stick to top when scrolling.
Summary bar sticks to top above the headers.

PERFORMANCE:
Table may have 500+ rows.
Use CSS will-change and avoid re-renders on scroll.
If row count exceeds 1000, use windowed rendering
(only render visible rows + buffer).
For 500 rows this is not needed — render all.

---

Implementation:

Create a new component: src/components/SideBySideDiffTable.tsx

Props:
{
  result: DiffResult
  schemaA: CsvSchema
  schemaB: CsvSchema
  rowsA: string[][]
  rowsB: string[][]
  fileNameA: string
  fileNameB: string
}

Internal logic:

1. Build a unified row list from DiffResult:

type UnifiedRow = {
  rowNumber: number
  type: 'unchanged' | 'modified' | 'added' | 'deleted'
  rowA: string[] | null    // null for added rows
  rowB: string[] | null    // null for deleted rows
  changedColumns: Set<string>  // columns that changed
}

2. For modified rows:
   - rowA = original values from rowsA
   - rowB = new values from rowsB
   - changedColumns = Set of column names from result.modifiedRows[n].changes

3. For added rows (in rowsB but not rowsA):
   - rowA = null (show "—" in all File A cells)
   - rowB = actual values from rowsB

4. For deleted rows (in rowsA but not rowsB):
   - rowA = actual values from rowsA
   - rowB = null (show "—" in all File B cells)

5. For unchanged rows:
   - rowA = values from rowsA
   - rowB = same values
   - changedColumns = empty Set

6. Sort unified rows by rowNumber ascending.

COLUMNS:
Use schemaA.columns for File A column headers.
Use schemaB.columns for File B column headers.
Common columns appear on both sides.
Columns only in A: appear on A side only, "—" on B side.
Columns only in B: "—" on A side, appear on B side.

STYLING:
Dark theme to match existing app.
Use plain CSS — no external UI library.
Table takes full width of container.
Horizontal scroll if columns overflow.
Row height: 36px minimum.
Font: monospace for data cells (csv data reads better).
Font size: 13px for data, 12px for headers.

Colours (dark theme):
  Background:          #0f172a
  Table header:        #1e293b
  Unchanged row:       #0f172a, opacity 0.5
  Modified row:        rgba(146, 64, 14, 0.3)   amber
  Modified cell A:     rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.4)   red tint
  Modified cell B:     rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.4)   green tint
  Added row:           rgba(20, 83, 45, 0.4)    green
  Deleted row:         rgba(127, 29, 29, 0.4)   red
  Border:              #1e293b
  Text:                #e2e8f0
  Muted text:          #64748b  (for "—" placeholders)
  Summary added:       #4ade80
  Summary deleted:     #f87171
  Summary modified:    #fb923c
  Summary unchanged:   #64748b

DIVIDER:
A 2px vertical divider between File A columns and
File B columns. Colour: #334155.
Makes the two sides visually distinct.

